-- U.K.’s Top Six Banks to Create 1.5 Billion-Pound Business Fund
-- B y   J o n   M e n o n   a n d   A n d r e w   M a c A s k i l l
-- 2010-10-13T15:47:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/top-six-u-k-banks-to-create-2-38-billion-fund-to-help-small-businesses.html
Britain’s six biggest banks will
start a 1.5 billion-pound ($2.4 billion) fund to help smaller
companies in getting financing.  HSBC Holdings Plc, Barclays Plc, Royal Bank of Scotland
Group Plc, Lloyds Banking Group Plc, Standard Chartered Plc and
Banco Santander SA’s U.K. unit will contribute to the fund
“over a number of years,” according to a report to be
published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jon Menon in London at 
